<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3803] Bundle#getResource always try to resolve the bundle</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3803</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think the behavior should be similar to Bundle#loadClass, i.e. only try to resolve the bundle if the bundle is in the INSTALLED state.  The spec says:  &quot;If this bundle&#8217;s state is INSTALLED, this method must attempt to resolve this bundle before attempting to get the specified resource. &quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12618720">FELIX-3803</key>
            <summary>Bundle#getResource always try to resolve the bundle</summary>
